Correcting alignment¶

In [9]:
from scipy import ndimage
In [10]:
def get_rotated_and_back(img):
    new_img = img.copy()
    new_img[:100] = 0
    new_img[-100:] = 0
    angle = 3
    # mask = nb.erode(img, 170)
    rotated = ndimage.rotate(new_img, -angle)
    rotated_back = ndimage.rotate(rotated, angle-1)
    return rotated, rotated_back


rotated, rotated_back = get_rotated_and_back(img)

def plot_sub_area_stats(ax=None):
    s = {
      "lines.linewidth": 2.0,
      "axes.edgecolor": "#bcbcbc",
      "patch.linewidth": 0.5,
      "legend.fancybox": True,
      "axes.prop_cycle": cycler('color', [
        "#348ABD",
        "#A60628",
        "#7A68A6",
        "#467821",
        "#CF4457",
        "#188487",
        "#E24A33"
      ]),
      "axes.facecolor": "#eeeeee",
      "axes.labelsize": "large",
      "axes.grid": True,
      "grid.linestyle": 'dashed',
      "grid.color": 'black',
      "grid.alpha": .2,
      "patch.edgecolor": "#eeeeee",
      "axes.titlesize": "x-large",
      "svg.fonttype": "path",
    }

    matplotlib.rcParams.update(s)
    font = {'size': 22}

    rc('text', usetex=False)
    rc('font', **font)
    cond = stats['Variation'] != '6.25% area'
    data = stats[cond].groupby(['file', 'Variation']).mean().reset_index()
    data = data.set_index(['Variation', 'file']).stack().rename('Statistic Value ($\mu m$)').reset_index()\
        .rename(columns = {"level_2": "Measure"})
    ax = sns.catplot(data=data, kind='bar',  height=1.3*8.27, aspect=11.7/8.27, 
                     x='Measure', y='Statistic Value ($\mu m$)', hue='Variation', ci=99, 
                     palette='CMRmap', alpha=.7, ax=ax)

def plot_subarea_colors(axes=None):

    a = stats.groupby(['file', 'Variation'])['ra'].agg(['mean', 'std', 'count'])
    res = a.groupby(level=-1).agg({'mean': 'mean', 'std': 'sum', 'count': 'sum'})

        [variation,
         nb.st.ttest_ind(
             create_random_normal(*res.loc[variation]),
             create_random_normal(*res.loc['Original'])
         ).pvalue] 
        for variation in res.index[:-1].values
    ], columns=['Variation', 'p-value']).assign(metric=metric)
    )
